ğŸ“˜ Task: Python List Operations
ğŸ§¾ Objectives
Practice basic list operations in Python.

Understand how to modify, extend, and sort lists.

Learn how to search for elements in a list.

ğŸ› ï¸ Instructions
Create an empty list called my_list.

Append the values 10, 20, 30, and 40 to the list.

Insert the value 15 at the second position (index 1).

Extend the list with [50, 60, 70].

Remove the last element from the list.

Sort the list in ascending order.

Find and print the index of the value 30 in the final list.

âœ… Expected Output

Index of 30: 4
Final list: [10, 15, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60]
ğŸ’¡ Notes
Use list.append() to add elements.

Use list.insert(index, value) to insert at a specific position.

Use list.extend() to combine two lists.

Use list.pop() to remove the last element.

Use list.sort() to sort the list.

Use list.index(value) to find the position of an element.

ğŸ’» Example Usage

$ python list_task.py
